The paper deals with consensus algorithms in distributed computing, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The problem of consensus on a convex polytope involves concepts from computational geometry and optimization, which are covered in the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Optimization and Control (cs.SY). The paper also involves game-theoretic analysis, which is covered in the sub-category of Game Theory and Economics (cs.GT). Finally, the paper presents an algorithm with a bound on its output, which involves information theory concepts, covered in the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT).
